<div class="container black drama">
	<h3>Team Cap</h3>
	<ul><li>A delegation may send one team only.</li><li>The team can comprise of 6-10 people.</li></ul>
	<h3>Procedure</h3>
	<ul><li>The drama section of the event will comprise of a total of two rounds.</li><li>Elimination round. (8-10 minutes)</li><li>Final round.(15-25 minutes)</li></ul>
	<h3>Rules</h3>
	<ul><li>Scripts can be in either Urdu, English, or a mix of both.</li><li>There should be no sensitive elements aimed towards religion, race, or any sensitive political topics.</li><li>Costumes, props and decorations will not be provided by the management team; participants are requested to bring such items with themselves.</li><li>The school or management team are not responsible for the loss or damage of any props/items.</li><li>Scripts cannot contain any vulgar language.</li><li>Time limits are 15-20 minutes; going over or under the time limit will result in point deduction.</li><li>A complete list of crew and cast members must be provided.</li><li>Any music needed must be downloaded onto a USB in an mp3 or an mp4 format, and given to the management team a day beforehand. The music cannot contain vulgar or explicit language or else it will not be used.</li><li>Inappropriate costumes will result in disqualification.</li></ul>
	<h3>Judging Criteria</h3>
	<ul><li>Script</li><li>Expressions</li><li>Direction</li><li>Originality</li></ul> 
	<h3>Awards</h3>
	<ul><li>Best Play (10 points)</li><li>Best Script (8 points)</li><li>Best Actor (5 points)</li></ul>
</div>